  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "GENERAL CLEANER",
  "description": "<p><strong>Company Overview</strong></p><p>We are a dynamic commercial maintenance and cleaning company with over 16 years of experience of track record in Singapore. We provide 100% satisfaction guarantee services to our clients and support their hygiene needs as well as a conducive and clean environment to work in.</p><p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>You will clean and maintain functional areas to ensure a hygienic and safe environment. You will manage waste disposal, prepare event spaces, and perform cleaning tasks as scheduled or directed. Your role requires you to work 6 days a week including weekends. </p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Clean and maintain office and functional areas by vacuuming, dusting, and wiping surfaces to ensure cleanliness and hygiene</li><li>Clean assigned toilets thoroughly to maintain sanitary conditions</li><li>Manage waste and recyclables by collecting and disposing of them in designated areas following proper procedures</li><li>Prepare auditorium by cleaning and setting up tables and chairs to meet hygiene and event standards</li><li>Perform ad-hoc cleaning tasks as scheduled or directed by supervisors or customers to support operational needs</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred competencies and qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>1-2 years of experience in a similar cleaning role in environments such as schools, condominiums, or factories</li><li>Ability to work independently with attention to detail and minimal supervision</li><li>Basic knowledge of cleaning chemicals and equipment to apply appropriate cleaning methods</li><li>Reliability, punctuality, and physical fitness to perform manual cleaning tasks effectively</li></ul><p><strong>Other Information</strong></p><ul><li>Competitive salary of S$2,200/month excluding overtime</li><li>Medical benefits, annual leave, and CPF contributions</li><li>Work schedule: 6 days per week with one weekday off</li><li>Working hours: 7.30am to 4.30pm</li><li>Eligibility: Singapore Citizens, Permanent Residents, and Long-Term Visit Pass holders only</li></ul>",
